Look what you do on a Raspberry Pi. If nothing else you will learn JAVA. Today we take JAVA back to the basics and away from the IDE. We will crate two classes in different packages. We will set the CLASSPATH variable to we gain access to the classes and we will import a class into our running client. With this done we can look at the main subject Bracket Exponents Division Multiplication Addition Subtract. This is the defined operator presence. if we need to control this order then we must use brackets to control the evaluation of mathematical operators.